      "text": "Computers, as Fuchs (1991: 3) provocatively remarks, \"are finally information transmitters, information receivers, and information processors par excellence. Taking this into account, their communication behavior differs from human communication behavior at most by precision and speed, when it comes to the access time for the processing and output of information (...)\". The computer is a (machine-)technology, which – just like persons of ongoing communication – \"(...) conveys to a sufficient extent both normal conformity and ongoing irritation (...)\" (Luhmann, 1992: 2). "
    },
