      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0ef01617de5d935e",
      "text": "Like persons, the computer provides signals that can be 'read' as information and messages in the communication process. This peculiar coupling of the computer to communication processes may be the reason why it is often formulated in everyday life as well as in social science communication contexts as a 'communication partner' that can be and is used to build up socio-technical interaction processes (cf. also Geser, 1989)."
